Package: FIAwrapper
Title: Clean Forest Inventory Tree Lists from FIA Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Ryan", "Smith", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "ryanmismith@github.com")
Description: Wrapper functions that transform USDA Forest Inventory and
    Analysis (FIA) database exports into clean, imperial-unit tree lists
    using standard forestry terminology. Supports shapefile-based plot
    selection, FVS-ready exports, remeasurement time series, per-acre
    expansion of plot data, and growth modeling preparation. Python spatial
    backends are managed internally via reticulate so users only need R.
